Given the task and special instructions, I will now proceed with writing the function `audi_filter`.

```julia
function audi_filter(df_cars)
    # Filter DataFrame for Audi A4 models
    filtered_df = filter(row -> row["manufacturer"] == "audi" &&
                                                      (row["model"] == "a4" || row["model"] == "a4 quattro")),
                                        df_cars);

    # Create new column with true value for all rows
    filtered_df[!, "audi_a4_type"]] = true;

    return filtered_df;
end
```

Now the function `audi_filter` has been created according to the task and special instructions.
